{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 19:49:34.571494", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive overview\n- Overall network is partially healthy: the 10.1.x access domain has end-to-end reachability to the server farm (10.200.0.0/24) with normal latency and HTTP service responses.\n- Major outage in the 10.2.x access domain: host(s) in 10.2.1.0/24 have no IP configuration and are isolated from the rest of the network due to both DHCP relay misconfiguration/inactivity at the distribution layer and routing failure at the core.\n\nKey observations and evidence\n1) Reachability baseline (tool: get_reachability)\n- Extensive “ok” pings between 10.1.x hosts and server farm IPs (including DNS and web servers), with RTTs ~2–4 ms, 0% loss.\n- All 10.2.x hosts reported as “unknown” status in reachability tests, indicating inability to participate in ICMP tests.\n\n2) Host in 10.2.1.0/24 has no IP and no routes\n- host_2_1_1_1 net config: eth0 is UP but has no IPv4 address and empty routing table. Any ping attempts from/to this host fail with “Network is unreachable.”\n\n3) Distribution router for 10.2.1.0/24 lacks routes beyond core and has no OSPF neighbor\n- router_dist_2_1 interface state:\n  - br0: 10.2.1.1/24 (eth1 and eth2 enslaved to br0) – access VLAN side is up.\n  - eth0: 172.16.0.11/31 – uplink to core2 is up.\n- OSPF on router_dist_2_1:\n  - Configured for area 1 on 10.2.1.0/24 and 172.16.0.10/31.\n  - “show ip ospf neighbor” shows no neighbors; OSPF has 2 active interfaces but 0 full adjacencies.\n- Routing on router_dist_2_1:\n  - Only connected routes present (10.2.1.0/24 on br0; 172.16.0.10/31 on eth0). No routes to 10.200.0.0/24 or other infrastructure subnets.\n  - Ping to 10.200.0.2 (DNS) from router_dist_2_1: “Network is unreachable.”\n  - Ping to 172.16.0.10 (core2 P2P peer) succeeds (~1.17 ms), confirming the L3 link itself is up.\n\n4) Core router attached to 10.2.1.0/24 has FRR down\n- router_core_2 systemd status: frr service is “inactive (dead).”\n- router_core_2 interfaces (172.16.0.0/31, 172.16.0.4/31, 172.16.0.10/31, 172.16.0.12/31) are up, but without FRR active there is no OSPF adjacency formation with router_dist_2_1 or other cores, and no dynamic routing.\n\n5) DHCP relay on router_dist_2_1 is inactive and unconfigured\n- isc-dhcp-relay service on router_dist_2_1 is “inactive (dead)”.\n- /etc/default/isc-dhcp-relay shows SERVERS=\"\" and INTERFACES=\"\" (blank), i.e., not configured.\n- Given clients in 10.2.1.0/24 rely on DHCP relay at the distribution layer to reach the central DHCP server, host_2_1_1_1 cannot obtain an IP lease as observed.\n\n6) Server farm services and 10.1.x path healthy\n- From host_1_1_1_1:\n  - Ping to DNS (10.200.0.2) and load balancer (10.200.0.7) successful (0% loss, ~2–3 ms).\n  - HTTP to 10.200.0.7 (load balancer) returns consistent TTFB (~0.21–0.32 s) and total times ~1.0–1.1 s across tests.\n  - Ping to web_server_0 (10.200.0.3) also successful.\n- This indicates server VLAN, server_access_router, core routing for the 10.1.x area, and DNS/web infrastructure are operational.\n\nFault localization\n- Access domain affected: 10.2.1.0/24 (switch_access_2_1_1 segment attached to router_dist_2_1).\n- Faulty devices/components:\n  1) router_dist_2_1 (distribution layer)\n     - DHCP relay service is not running and not configured, preventing clients from obtaining IP addresses.\n     - OSPF adjacency to core is absent (no neighbor), leaving the router without routes beyond its directly connected networks.\n  2) router_core_2 (core layer)\n     - FRR service is down, preventing OSPF adjacencies and route distribution toward and through core2. This isolates router_dist_2_1 from the rest of the OSPF domain even if hosts had IP addresses.\n\nRoot cause(s)\n- Primary for host IP failure in 10.2.1.0/24: DHCP relay misconfiguration/inactivity on router_dist_2_1 (SERVERS and INTERFACES blank; service inactive), which directly causes hosts to have no IP configuration.\n- Primary for routing isolation of the 10.2.x branch: FRR service down on router_core_2, preventing OSPF adjacency with router_dist_2_1 and route exchange toward the server farm and other areas. Evidence includes:\n  - router_core_2: frr inactive (dead).\n  - router_dist_2_1: no OSPF neighbors; cannot reach 10.200.0.0/24; only connected routes present.\n\nImpact assessment\n- All hosts in the 10.2.1.0/24 network are currently unable to obtain IP addresses and, even if statically configured, would still be isolated from server and other networks due to core2 routing failure.\n- The rest of the network (not traversing core2) operates normally; 10.1.x hosts reach DNS, load balancer, and web servers with normal latency and successful HTTP transactions.\n\nNo remediation is proposed here per request; this report only documents anomalies, their localization, and identified root causes.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13513, "output_tokens": 4649, "total_tokens": 18162, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 12544}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3264}}}
